Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}. Toss on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}, half the @Turkish spice blend{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Toss @grape tomatoes{4} on empty side with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until bell pepper is browned and softened and tomatoes begin to burst, ~{15-17%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets; roast tomatoes on middle rack and bell pepper on top rack.

Meanwhile, trim and halve @Persian cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Pick and roughly chop fronds from @dill{1/4%bunch}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, half the dill, a squeeze of lemon juice, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, salt, and pepper. In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice to taste, salt, and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

In a #small pot{}, combine 3/4 cup water, @vegetable stock concentrate{1}, remaining Turkish spice, @butter{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then stir in @couscous{1/2%cup}. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand until water has absorbed and couscous is tender, at least ~{5%minutes} or until ready to serve.

In a third small bowl, combine @Sabra Classic Hummus{4%tbsp} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp} to taste.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in lemon zest, salt, and pepper; divide between bowls. Top with bell pepper, tomatoes, cucumber salad, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and hummus. Drizzle with lemon cream and sprinkle with remaining dill. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.